+# FIFA Paper Replication
+
+This repo contains the published paper, a LaTeX reproduction, and a Python
+replication script for the econometric analysis.
+
+## Quick start
+1) Create a virtual environment and install dependencies:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m venv .venv
+source .venv/bin/activate
+pip install -r requirements.txt
+```
+
+2) Prepare a panel dataset (CSV) with these columns:
+- `country`, `year`, `confed`
+- `fifa_points`
+- `gdp_pc`, `gdp_pc_sq`
+- `pop`, `pop_sq`
+- `trade`, `infl`, `oil`, `leb`
+- `club`
+- `urbpop`, `urbpop_sq`
+
+3) Run the replication script:
+
+```bash
+python3 scripts/replicate_stata.py --data data/analysis/panel.csv
+```
+
+Results will be written to the `results/` folder as CSV summaries.
+
+## Notes
+- Python 3.8+ is required for the replication script.
+- The original Stata do files are missing, so the replication relies on the
+  specification in the paper and Stata 8/9 defaults.
+- Equation (3) uses a fixed-effects IV approach with urban population as the
+  instrument for `club`.

+        "        out = df.copy()\n",
+        "        for col in cols:\n",
+        "            overall = out[col].mean()\n",
+        "            ent_mean = out.groupby(entity)[col].transform(\"mean\")\n",
+        "            time_mean = out.groupby(time)[col].transform(\"mean\")\n",
+        "            out[col] = out[col] - ent_mean - time_mean + overall\n",
+        "        return out\n",
+        "\n",
+        "    def _drop_absorbed(panel, exog):\n",
+        "        names = list(panel.index.names)\n",
+        "        if len(names) < 2 or names[0] is None or names[1] is None:\n",
+        "            return exog, []\n",
+        "\n",
+        "        entity, time = names[0], names[1]\n",
+        "        work = panel.reset_index()\n",
+        "        demeaned = two_way_demean(work, exog, entity, time)\n",
+        "        dropped = []\n",
+        "        keep = []\n",
+        "        for col in exog:\n",
+        "            if demeaned[col].var() <= 1e-12:\n",
+        "                dropped.append(col)\n",
+        "            else:\n",
+        "                keep.append(col)\n",
+        "        return keep, dropped\n",
+        "\n",
+        "    def fit_fe_ols(panel, dep, exog):\n",
+        "        keep, dropped = _drop_absorbed(panel, exog)\n",
+        "        if dropped:\n",
+        "            print(\"Dropped absorbed variables: {0}\".format(\", ".join(dropped)))\n",
+        "        if not keep:\n",
+        "            raise ValueError(\"All regressors absorbed by fixed effects.\")\n",
+        "\n",
+        "        y = panel[dep]\n",
+        "        X = panel[keep]\n",
+        "        model = PanelOLS(y, X, entity_effects=True, time_effects=True)\n",
+        "        return model.fit(cov_type=\"clustered\", cluster_entity=True, debiased=True)\n",
+        "\n",
+        "    def fit_fe_iv(df, dep, exog, endog, instr, entity, time):\n",

+        "        work = two_way_demean(work, [dep] + exog + [endog] + instr, entity, time)\n",
+        "\n",
+        "        y = work[dep]\n",
+        "        keep_exog = [c for c in exog if work[c].var() > 1e-12]\n",
+        "        if not keep_exog:\n",
+        "            raise ValueError(\"All exogenous regressors absorbed by fixed effects.\")\n",
+        "\n",
+        "        endog_v = work[endog]\n",
+        "        if endog_v.var() <= 1e-12:\n",

+        "            raise ValueError(\"All instruments absorbed by fixed effects.\")\n",
+        "\n",
+        "        X = work[keep_exog]\n",
+        "        Z = work[keep_instr]\n",
+        "\n",
